 to receive a warning message when you exit the application.","pos":[1859,1933]},{"content":"This message helps guarantee that you don't exit the program unintentionally.","pos":[1934,2011]},{"content":"Automatically apply cell underline in column headers","pos":[2044,2096]},{"content":"Select whether to insert an underline in the cell of a new column header.","pos":[2106,2179]},{"content":"Management Reporter files location","pos":[2213,2247]},{"content":"Specify the default location for files.","pos":[2257,2296]},{"content":"The application uses the default location when you export building block groups.","pos":[2297,2377]},{"pos":[2410,2418],"content":"See also","linkify":"See also","nodes":[{"content":"See also","pos":[0,8]}]},{"pos":[2429,2562],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Financial reporting for Microsoft Dynamics ERP<ept id=\"p1\">](http://ax.help.dynamics.com/en/wiki/management-reporter-for-microsoft-dynamics-erp/)</ept>","source":"[Financial reporting for Microsoft Dynamics ERP](http://ax.help.dynamics.com/en/wiki/management-reporter-for-microsoft-dynamics-erp/)"}],"content":"---\n# required metadata\n\ntitle: User preferences in financial report designer | Microsoft Docs\ndescription: This article explains how to set user preferences to customize your user interactions in financial report designer and control the initial sign-in experience. You can also control how individual reports, the report library, and the default file locations are displayed. \nauthor: annbe\nmanager: AnnBe\nms.date: 2016-02-04 19:44:33\nms.topic: article\nms.prod: \nms.service: Dynamics365Operations\nms.technology: \n\n# optional metadata\n\nkeywords: FinancialReports\n# ROBOTS: \naudience: Application User\n# ms.devlang: \n# ms.reviewer: \nms.suite: Released- Dynamics AX application 7.0.1\n# ms.tgt_pltfrm: \nms.custom: 31161\nms.assetid: 0480c814-87f3-4d77-b6b7-335be3a110d6\n# ms.region: \n# ms.industry: \nms.author: RobinARH\n\n---\n\n# User preferences in financial report designer\n\nSet user preferences\n--------------------\n\n1.  In Report Designer, on the **Tools** menu, click **Options**.\n2.  In the **Options** dialog box, select your preferences.\n3.  Click **OK**.\n\n## Options dialog box options\n<table>\n<colgroup>\n<col width=\"50%\" />\n<col width=\"50%\" />\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"header\">\n<th>User option</th>\n<th>Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td>At startup</td>\n<td>Select what you see when Management Reporters starts. Select one of the following options:\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Load last loaded report</strong> – Open the last report that you viewed.</li>\n<li><strong>Show Open window</strong> – Open the <strong>Open</strong> window. The <strong>Open</strong> window provides a search window that you can use to quickly find building blocks.</li>\n<li><strong>Show empty environment</strong> – Open an empty designer window.</li>\n</ul></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td>Display confirmation before exiting Management Reporter</td>\n<td>Select whether to receive a warning message when you exit the application. This message helps guarantee that you don't exit the program unintentionally.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td>Automatically apply cell underline in column headers</td>\n<td>Select whether to insert an underline in the cell of a new column header.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td>Management Reporter files location</td>\n<td>Specify the default location for files. The application uses the default location when you export building block groups.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n\n\nSee also\n--------\n\n[Financial reporting for Microsoft Dynamics ERP](http://ax.help.dynamics.com/en/wiki/management-reporter-for-microsoft-dynamics-erp/)\n\n"}